    // Modals
    #scoreNrModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1' aria-labelledby='scoreNrModalLabel' aria-hidden='true')
        .modal-dialog
            .modal-content
                .modal-header(style="background-color:rgb(0, 107, 161)").text-white
                    h5#scoreNrModalLabel.modal-title The Responsible Numerical score
                    button.btn-close(type='button' data-bs-dismiss='modal' aria-label='Close')
                .modal-body
                    p  The NR Score (Responsible Numerical Score) is an indicator that allows the environmental impact of the website to be assessed. It varies between 0 and 100, the higher the score, the more eco-responsible the analyzed site is. The NR indicator classifies a site according to 5 categories (A, B, C, D, E, F, G), from the lowest to the highest impact.
    #complexiteModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1' aria-labelledby='complexiteModalLabel' aria-hidden='true')
        .modal-dialog
            .modal-content
                .modal-header(style="background-color:rgb(0, 107, 161)").text-white
                    h5#complexiteModalLabel.modal-title The complexity
                    button.btn-close(type='button' data-bs-dismiss='modal' aria-label='Close')
                .modal-body
                    p The complexity of a web page is an indicator defined by the number of elements (example: HTML tags) that compose it. The more elements the web site has, the more complex it will be.
    #charge_serveurModal.modal.fade(tabindex='-1' aria-labelledby='charge_serveurModalLabel' aria-hidden='true')
